UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc4='In tribute to King Varian Wrynn $Bknown to some as LO\'GOSH the "Ghost Wolf"$B$BHis miraculous return from long years of exile and hardship has ignited a new fire of spirit and courage within the Alliance.$B$BWe shall march boldly into these perilous lands holding his valor and his tenacity in our hearts.$B$B$B- Highlord Bolvar Fordragon$B' WHERE word_id = 126093;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc4='My men report that a small group of Forsaken have broken ground on a camp along the hillside to the north. On the other side of the hill, the Alliance have apparently begun the construction of a much larger base.$B$BThe admiral says that we should leave them be. There are other Horde forces gathered to the west that would surely come to their aid if we were to attack. I don\'t feel good about it, but I see the logic in his reasoning.$B$BThe first phase of construction is done. Admiral Westwind has ordered a group of my men to establish a toehold further to the north. He wouldn\'t go into detail, claiming that he was being "guided" to do so.$B$BWe caught four spies from the Forsaken town, Venomspite, this afternoon. I\'m going to have LeCraft torture them for information. If we only caught four, how many more have slipped in amongst us?$B$BWhy do I feel as if things are beginning to unravel?' WHERE word_id = 126889;
UPDATE trans_words SET content_loc4='Day 1: The human scum seem blissfully unaware of my presence here, as intended. They\'re ripe for bombing, and it should only be a matter of time before I\'ve charted out their position.$BDay 2: Charting complete - a trivial task for such an accomplished fellow as myself. Why I got stuck with this job is beyond me - they should have J-Y C. do it. That ridiculous accent should have been justification enough. $BDay 3: First breath of air is finally getting a bit stale. Perhaps I should surface momentarily for another in a few days. Still bored to tears - where is that blasted signal?$B< The ranting continues ... >' WHERE word_id = 126094;
